<div style="border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#fbfdff;padding:18px 18px 16px 18px;">
<div style="font-size:13px;font-weight:800;color:#5b6b88;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:6px;">Asset Information Model</div>
<div style="border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:14px;background:#ffffff;padding:14px 16px;margin-top:10px;font-size:13px;color:#5b6b88;">
<p data-pasted="true">The Asset Information Requirements are detailed in the Scope.</p>
<p>The Lead Appointed Party, operator, operations team or facility manager should confirm that all project information and data for operational purposes have been transferred from the<strong> Project Information Model (PIM)</strong> to the <strong>Asset Information Model (AIM). </strong></p>
<p style="margin:12px 0 0 0;color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;" data-pasted="true">The format, structure, and level of information required for the AIM shall align with the information requirements defined in the Scope.</p>
</div>
<p style="margin:12px 0 0 0;color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">Where this is not the case, the design and construction team should take action to ensure there is no further delay in transferring the required information and data.</p>
</div></div></div></div></div></div></div>